@startuml 05f_StateDiagram_AppState

skinparam backgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor     #ffffff
    BorderColor         #000000
    BorderThickness     1.5
    FontName            Arial
    FontSize            11
    FontStyle           plain
    ArrowColor          #000000
    ArrowThickness      1.2
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor     #ffffff
    BorderColor         #000000
    FontName            Arial
    FontSize            9
}
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial

' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
title State 5.6 — AppState  [Session Lifecycle]
' Source  : AppState singleton  (Common layer)
'           AppState._currentUser : UserDTO?  (private)
'           AppState.CurrentUser property (public)
'           AppState.IsLoggedIn bool (public)
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

' ── States ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
state "NotAuthenticated\n(CurrentUser = null,\n IsLoggedIn = false)" as NotAuth
state "Authenticated\n(CurrentUser ≠ null,\n IsLoggedIn = true)" as Auth
state "LockedOut\n(LoginThrottleService:\n ≥ 5 failed attempts,\n locked 5 minutes)" as Locked

' ── Application startup ───────────────────────────────────────
[*] --> NotAuth : Application starts\n(Program.cs — Build() + Run())\n[AppState.Instance.CurrentUser = null]

' ── Login paths: NotAuthenticated → Authenticated ─────────────
NotAuth --> Auth : UserBLL.LoginAsync(username, password)\n[UserDTO.IsActive = true AND\n SecurityHelper.VerifyPassword(input, hash) = true]\n/ AppState.Instance.CurrentUser = UserDTO\n  SystemAuditHelper.LogAsync(userId, "LOGIN", "User", userId)

NotAuth --> Auth : UserBLL.LoginWithFaceIDAsync(username)\n[UserDTO.IsActive = true AND\n FaceIdManager.CompareHistogram() ≥ AppConfig.FaceId.Threshold]\n/ AppState.Instance.CurrentUser = UserDTO

' ── Lockout path ──────────────────────────────────────────────
NotAuth --> Locked : LoginThrottleService.RecordFailure(username)\n[RecordFailure count ≥ MaxAttempts (default = 5)]\n/ LoginThrottleService timer starts\n  (LockoutMinutes = 5, from AppConfig)

' ── Lockout expiry ────────────────────────────────────────────
Locked --> NotAuth : LoginThrottleService timer elapsed\n(LockoutMinutes × 60 seconds)\n/ _attempts[username] cleared

' ── Logout paths: Authenticated → NotAuthenticated ─────────────
Auth --> NotAuth : UserBLL.LogoutAsync()\n/ AppState.Instance.Logout()  [CurrentUser = null]\n  [Note: no LOGOUT audit log — only LOGIN is recorded\n   via SystemAuditHelper.LogAsync]

Auth --> NotAuth : SessionTimeoutService timer fires\n[Idle for 30 minutes]\n/ SessionTimeoutService.Stop()\n  AppState.Instance.Logout()\n  Login form shown

' ── Application exit ──────────────────────────────────────────
Auth    --> [*] : Application closed\n(MainForm.FormClosing)\n[EmailSmtpHelper.Shutdown() called]
NotAuth --> [*] : Application closed\n(Login form closed)
Locked  --> [*] : Application closed\nduring lockout

' ── Notes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
note right of Auth
  AppState is «singleton»:
  AppState.Instance (double-check lock pattern)
  CurrentUser exposes logged-in UserDTO.
  RoleID in UserDTO controls role-based UI:
  - IsReadOnlyForRole() → Director sees dashboard only.
  - Each UC reads AppState.Instance.CurrentUser.RoleID.
  [UserDTO.IsActive = false] accounts are REJECTED
  at UserBLL.LoginAsync() — they never reach Authenticated.
end note

note right of Locked
  LoginThrottleService is «static»:
  - _attempts : Dictionary<string, (int Count, DateTime LockUntil)>
  - MaxAttempts   = AppConfig.Login.MaxAttempts (default 5)
  - LockoutMinutes = AppConfig.Login.LockoutMinutes (default 5)
  IsLockedOut(username, out remaining) returns true
  when LockUntil > DateTime.Now.
end note

note bottom of NotAuth
  SessionTimeoutService is «static»:
  - Started in MainForm constructor:
      SessionTimeoutService.Start(minutes: 30, onTimeout: () => ...)
  - Reset() called on any user interaction.
  - Stop() called on manual logout.
end note

@enduml
